[*Dedicated to E.B.Vinberg on the occasion of his 70th birthday*]{}

Introduction
============

Let $M=G/H$ be a homogeneous space of a compact connected Lie group $G$, where $H$ is the stable subgroup of the base point $o$. $M$ is called [*multiplicity free*]{} if the quasiregular representation of $G$ in $C(M)$ contains every irreducible representation of $G$ with a multiplicity $0$ or $1$. This remarkable class of homogeneous spaces can be characterized by each of the following properties (see [@Vi] or [@W07]; the noncompact case is more complicated):

-   $M$ is [*commutative*]{}, i.e., the algebra of all invariant differential operators on $M$ is commutative;

-   $(G,H)$ is a [*Gelfand pair*]{}, i.e., the convolution algebra of all left and right $H$-invariant functions in $L^1(G)$ (or measures) is commutative;

-   a generic $G$-orbit in the cotangent bundle $T^*M$ is coisotropic (a submanifold $L$ of a symplectic manifold is called [*coisotropic*]{} if $T_pL^\bot\subseteq T_pL$ for each $p\in L$);

-   $M$ is [*weakly commutative*]{} (the Poisson algebra $C^\infty(T^*M)$ is commutative);

-   $M$ is [*weakly symmetric*]{} (there exists an automorphism ${{\mathord{\varkappa}}}$ of $G$ such that ${{\mathord{\varkappa}}}(g)\in Hg^{-1}H$ for all $g\in G$);

